The paper is about improving the performance of cross-project defect prediction, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed method involves mapping instances based on distribution characteristics, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques such as clustering and classification (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also deals with the issue of imbalanced feature sets, which is a common problem in data analysis and machine learning (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of public defect data sets, which is related to the topic of open data and data sharing (cs.SI).
